DefaultReaderConfiguration.fullDescription: Gathers power monitoring events from InfraStuXure racks and UPS Network Management Cards.

file.toolTipText: Directory or path to read from

string.toolTipText: Hostname of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

integer.toolTipText: Port number of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

select.toolTipText: Data routing (normalized alerts to Manager and/or raw data to nDepth)

integer.toolTipText: Number of seconds between log reads

FastPattern.description: 1, ServiceInfo: InRow RC, violation cleared
2, ServiceWarning: InRow RC, violation exists
3, ServiceInfo: APC, Test Syslog
4, PolicyModify: System, Configuration change
5, PolicyModify: System, SNMP configuration change
6, PolicyModify: System, SSL enabled
7, UserLogoff: System, (web|ftp) user logged out
8, UserLogon: System, (web|ftp) user logged in
9, AuthSuspicious: System, Detected an unauthorized user
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+(?: System:)? Detected an unauthorized user attempting to access the (?:Web|SNMP|FTP) interface from [\d.]+(?:\s\[[^]]+\])?\.? 0x[A-F\d]+

FastFormatter.condition: Detected an unauthorized user attempting to access the (.+) interface from.*

FastPattern.description: 10, SystemReboot: System, Warmstart
11, SystemReboot: System, Restarting
12, PolicyModify: System: Set Daylight Saving Time
13, ServiceInfo: UPS, Passed internal self-test
14, ServiceInfo: UPS, Restored local management interface
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: Restored the local network management interface-to-UPS communication\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 15, ServiceInfo: UPS, A discharged/low battery condition
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: A (?:discharged|low) battery condition no longer exists\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 16, ServiceInfo: UPS, A faulty battery
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: A faulty battery no longer exists\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 17, ServiceInfo: UPS, No longer on battery
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: No longer on battery power\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 18, ServiceInfo: UPS, Runtime calibration canceled
19, ServiceInfo: UPS, Started a runtime calibration
20, ServiceInfo: UPS, Started a self-test
21, ServiceWarning: UPS, At least one faulty battery
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: At least one faulty battery exists\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 22, ServiceWarning: UPS, Failed a self-test
23, ServiceWarning: UPS, On battery power
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: On battery power in response to (?:an input power problem|distorted input|rapid change of input)\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 24, ServiceWarning: UPS, The battery power is too low
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: The battery power is too low (?:to continue )?to support the load; .+\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 25, ServiceWarning: System, RMS failed to send emai
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ System: RMS failed to send email\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 26, ServiceStart: System, Network service System IP
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ System: Network service started. System IP is [\d.]+ from manually configured settings\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastFormatter.condition: Network service started. System IP is ([\d.]+) from manually configured settings
FastFormatter.format: Network service started. System IP is "$7" from manually configured settings

FastPattern.description: 27, ServiceStart: System, Network service IPv6 assigned
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ System: Network service started. IPv6 address [A-F\d:]+ assigned by link-local autoconfiguration\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastFormatter.condition: Network service started. IPv6 address ([A-F\d:]+) assigned by link-local autoconfiguration
FastFormatter.format: Network service started. IPv6 address "$7" assigned by link-local autoconfiguration

FastPattern.description: 28, ServiceInfo: UPS, Completed runtime calibration
29, ServiceInfo: System, Network Interface restarted
30, ServiceInfo: UPS, The load no longer exceeds capacity
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: The load no longer exceeds \d+% of rated capacity\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 31, ServiceWarning: UPS, The load exceeds capacity
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: The load exceeds \d+% of rated capacity\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 32, ServiceInfo: UPS, No longer compensating
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: No longer compensating for a \S+ input voltage\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 33, ServiceWarning: UPS, Compensating for low/high voltage
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: Compensating for a \S+ input voltage\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 34, SystemStatus: System, NTP update
35, ServiceInfo: Switched Rack PDU, Device configuration change
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ Switched Rack PDU: Device configuration +change\. Display orientation\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 36, ServiceInfo: Switched Rack PDU, Outlet configuration change
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ Switched Rack PDU: Outlet configuration change\. Outlet Name on outlet #\d+ \(.+\)\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 37, SystemStatus: Switched Rack PDU, Outlet on/off
38, SystemStatus: System, Set fan speed
39, SystemReboot: System, Coldstart
40, ServiceInfo: Switched Rack PDU, Communications established
41, SystemStatus: Power for switched group is turned on/off
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: The power for switched outlet [^,]+, [^,]+, is now turned (?:on|off)

FastPattern.description: 42, ServiceInfo: UPS, MIB UPS test completed
43, ServiceWarning: UPS, input voltage or frequency problem prevents switching
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: An input voltage or frequency problem prevents switching to bypass mode

FastPattern.description: 44, ServiceInfo: UPS, input voltage or frequency problem no longer prevents switching
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: An input voltage or frequency problem no longer prevents switching to bypass mode

FastPattern.description: 45, ServiceWarning: UPS, phase synchronization fault exists
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: A phase synchronization fault exists

FastPattern.description: 46, ServiceInfo: UPS, phase synchronization fault no longer exists
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: A phase synchronization fault no longer exists

FastPattern.description: 47, ServiceWarning: UPS, bypass in response
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: In bypass in response to (?:an internal hardware fault|the bypass switch at the UPS)

FastPattern.description: 48, ServiceInfo: UPS, No longer in bypass
49, ServiceWarning: UPS, output voltage is outside limits
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: The output voltage is outside its defined limits

FastPattern.description: 50, ServiceInfo: UPS, output voltage is no longer outside limits
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: The output voltage is no longer outside its defined limits

FastPattern.description: 51, SystemStatus: System, Interface state
52, ServiceInfo: Switched Rack PDU, Low load
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ Switched Rack PDU: Low load(?: cleared)?\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 53, ServiceWarning: Switched Rack PDU, Communications lost
54, ServiceInfo: UPS; site wiring fault
56, ServiceWarning: UPS, battery is not installed properly
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: The battery is not installed properly\. 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 55, ServiceInfo: UPS, battery is now installed; Bypass not in range
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ UPS: (?:The battery is now installed\.|Bypass not in range .*) 0x[A-Fa-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: InternalNewToolData: InRow RC, unmatched data
InternalNewToolData: APC, unmatched data
InternalNewToolData: Switched Rack PDU, unmatched data
NullAlert: the ultimate black hole
